BP has continued its divestment programme by selling $5.55bn worth of Gulf of Mexico assets to US group Plains Exploration.The deal includes the Marlin, Dorado and King fields, as well as BP's stakes in Horn Mountain and Holstein. It brings the total proceeds from the sale programme instigated after the Deepwater Horizon disaster to $32bn, out of a total target of $38bn. BP's chief executive Bob Dudley said:Analysts said the company had received a good price for the assets, and BP's shares have added 2.85p to 437.55p. Peter Hutton at RBC Capital Markets said: